<div id="review_1270489292" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1270489292" />
    <a title="Erika" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2496369-erika"><img alt="Erika" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1542059212p2/2496369.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1270489292?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erika" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erika" href="/user/show/2496369-erika">Erika</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2496369-erika?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1270489292" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2702556049359475579">Favourite poems: &quot;Heart&apos;s Needle&quot;, &quot;Home Town&quot;, &quot;The Cardinal&quot;, &quot;The Campus on the Hill&quot;, and &quot;April Inventory&quot;<br/>I don&apos;t usually like confessional poems, but I read an interview with Snodgrass published in the 80s and was drawn to this work because of it. While I still find confessional poets self-indulgent, this work is vital to understanding the nuances of that genre. What I enjoyed best was that he uses simple words and phrases to comment on strange and complex emotions.</span>
  <span id="freeText2702556049359475579" style="display:none">Favourite poems: "Heart's Needle", "Home Town", "The Cardinal", "The Campus on the Hill", and "April Inventory"<br />I don't usually like confessional poems, but I read an interview with Snodgrass published in the 80s and was drawn to this work because of it. While I still find confessional poets self-indulgent, this work is vital to understanding the nuances of that genre. What I enjoyed best was that he uses simple words and phrases to comment on strange and complex emotions.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2702556049359475579" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


